This paper proposes a new Bayesian optimization algorithm that can handle structured data using topological information extracted by persistent homology. The paper focuses on finding optimal solutions for material structures and neural network structures, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also utilizes persistent homology, which is a topological data analysis method, and proposes a new algorithm that can handle multiple types of topological information. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are sub-categories that often use topological data analysis methods.
